!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html;charset=utf-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    %title Simple Atoms Model
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/modernizr/modernizr.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript"}
      if (!Modernizr.svg) { window.location = '../../browser-upgrade.html'; }
    %link{:href => "../examples.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/d3/d3.v2.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/jquery/jquery.min.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/science.js/science.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/science.js/science.stats.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "http://use.typekit.com/hdw8ayt.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript"}
      try{Typekit.load();}catch(e){}
    %link{:href => "http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400italic,700italic,300italic,400,300,700&subset=latin,greek,latin-ext", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
    %link{:href => "application.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
  %body
    #header
      %a#logo(href="http://www.concord.org/")
        %img(src="../../resources/layout/cc-logo.png")
      %h1
        %a(href="http://lab.dev.concord.org/examples/simple-atoms-model-controls-in-text/simple-atoms-model-controls-in-text.html") Simple Atoms Model with Model Controls in Text
      %img#fullscreen(class="size-full wp-image-1880" src="../../resources/layout/fullscreen.gif")
    #content
      #viz
        .top
          .square
            %img{:src => "../../resources/aspect-ratio-1x1.png"}
            #molecule-container
          .therm
            #thermometer
            #therm_text
      #description-right
        %p
          Simulation of 50 atoms modeled with Coulomb forces from electric charge and the
          Lennard-Jones Potential which models the forces between neutral atoms. Atoms with
          opposite charges attract, atoms with the same charge repel each other.
        %p
          Try turning off the Coulomb particle force interaction to see how collections of
          neutral atoms behave.
        .component_group
          .slider_container
            Force Interactions
            .slider_content
              Coulomb
              %input(id="coulomb-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox")
            .below
              %input(id="lennard-jones-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox" checked)
        %p
          Also try adjusting the strength of the Lennard-Jones
          %b van der Waals attraction:
        .component_group
          .slider_container
            Intermolecular Attraction
            .slider_content
              #attraction_slider
            .left_half
              weaker
            .right_half
              stronger
            .below
              Attractive Force
        %p
          Make the model cold enough and the atoms will condense and form clumps. Heat it up
          and the atoms will overcome the attractive forces, the clumps will break up and the
          atoms will form a gas.
        .component_group
          .slider_container
            Change Temperature
            .content
              %div{:style=> "width: 10em; height: 2em; display: inline-block; margin: 0.5em"}
                %button#cool_button(type="button" class="left_edge" value="colder")colder
                %button#heat_button(type="button" class="right_edge" value="hotter")hotter

    %script{:src => "../../lab/lab.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "application.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
